Sentencas: Drop-on-demand (DOD) inkjet printing has great potential for fabricating miniature ceramic devices that are currently constructed by more complicated, time consuming, and costly procedures.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions

Sentencas: In this study, micro La(0.6)Sr(0.4)Feo(0.8)CO(0.2)O(3) (LSFC) patterns are crafted via DOD inkjet printing.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions

Sentencas: A dilute solid-solvent colloidal ink suspension composed of LSFC, a common solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode material, suspended in a-terpineol solvent, was printed with multiple, sequential inkjet passes.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions

Sentencas: Critical process parameters were identified and tuned to achieve acceptable layer to layer deposition accuracy.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions

Sentencas: Micro 0-D dots and micro 1-D lines with x/y dimensions <100 mu m and z-axis dimensions <1 mu m were demonstrated.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions

Sentencas: Addition of ethyl cellulose to the ink resulted in unique 'volcano' features which may benefit miniature SOFCs with a density shift between the feature's center and ridge.
Titulo: Controlling micro ceramic patterns via multiple/sequential drop-on-demand inkjet printing of dilute colloidal suspensions
